<subSubSection pageId="45" pageNumber="46" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="45.[533,1536,1192,1771]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[565,669,1401,1425]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Remarks:</emphasis>
The species closely resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Temminck, 1840" authorityName="Temminck" authorityYear="1840" box="[991,1406,1400,1425]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Arielulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="circumdatus">
<emphasis box="[991,1218,1400,1424]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Arielulus circumdatus</emphasis>
Temminck, 1840
</taxonomicName>
but has smaller forearms, post-palatal extension, toothrows and rostrum [
<bibRefCitation author="Hill JE" box="[1230,1268,1435,1459]" journalOrPublisher="Bull Br Mus.: Zool." pageId="45" pageNumber="46" pagination="21 - 42" part="23" refId="ref43583" refString="140. Hill JE. The Gunong Benom Expedition 1967. 4. New records of Malayan bats, with taxonomic notes and the description of a new Pipistrellus. Bull Br Mus.: Zool. 1972; 23: 21 - 42." title="The Gunong Benom Expedition 1967. 4. New records of Malayan bats, with taxonomic notes and the description of a new Pipistrellus" type="journal article" year="1972">140</bibRefCitation>
]. Heller and Volleth [
<bibRefCitation author="Heller KG &amp; Volleth M." box="[1500,1525,1435,1459]" journalOrPublisher="J Zoolog Syst Evol Res." pageId="45" pageNumber="46" pagination="65 - 77" part="22" refId="ref40096" refString="53. Heller KG, Volleth M. Taxonomic position of &quot; Pipistrellus societatis &quot; Hill, 1972 and the karyological characteristics of the genus Eptesicus (Chiroptera: Vespertilionidae). J Zoolog Syst Evol Res. 1984; 22 (1): 65 - 77." title="Taxonomic position of &quot; Pipistrellus societatis &quot; Hill, 1972 and the karyological characteristics of the genus Eptesicus (Chiroptera: Vespertilionidae)" type="journal article" year="1984">53</bibRefCitation>
] considered 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hill" baseAuthorityYear="1972" box="[656,778,1470,1494]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Arielulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="societatis">
<emphasis box="[656,674,1470,1493]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[685,778,1470,1493]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">societatis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Temminck" authorityYear="1840" box="[830,986,1470,1494]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Arielulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="circumdatus">
<emphasis box="[830,848,1470,1493]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[859,986,1470,1494]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">circumdatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to be conspecific with the former being the lowland subspecies of the latter but this was refuted by Hill and Francis [
<bibRefCitation author="Hill JE &amp; Francis CM" box="[1209,1247,1505,1529]" journalOrPublisher="Bull Br Mus." pageId="45" pageNumber="46" pagination="305 - 329" part="47" refId="ref45009" refString="173. Hill JE, Francis CM. New bats (Mammalia: Chiroptera) and new records of bats from Borneo and Malaya. Bull Br Mus. 1984; 47 (5): 305 - 329." title="New bats (Mammalia: Chiroptera) and new records of bats from Borneo and Malaya" type="journal article" year="1984">173</bibRefCitation>
] on the basis of morphological characteristics (see remarks on the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hill &amp; Harrison" authorityYear="1986" box="[1047,1140,1539,1563]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Arielulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1047,1140,1539,1563]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Arielulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Both are recognised as distinct species by Simmons [
<bibRefCitation author="Simmons NB" box="[726,751,1574,1598]" editor="Wilson DE &amp; Reeder DM" journalOrPublisher="Johns Hopkins University Press, Baltimore" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" pagination="312 - 529" refId="ref42036" refString="98. Simmons NB. Order chiroptera. In: Wilson DE, Reeder DM, editors. Mammal species of the world: a taxonomic and geographic reference. Johns Hopkins University Press, Baltimore; 2005. pp. 312 - 529." title="Order chiroptera" type="book chapter" volumeTitle="Mammal species of the world: a taxonomic and geographic reference" year="2005">98</bibRefCitation>
].
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="45.[533,1536,1192,1771]" box="[565,834,1609,1633]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[565,710,1609,1633]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">IUCN status:</emphasis>
